@zhenggen-xu  Just to clarify,  empty check for producerState table probably should be done after re-start.  
For pre-shutdown, applications don't know when orchagent will stop consuming the data and go shutdown.   

But after restore phase, orchagent will start picking up data using consumerstate api, we can expect any buffered data by producerstate before shutdown will be consumed quickly.

my proposal is to have a table level resync operation. The operation has three stages, 1) prepare resync. 2) populate the full table. 3) finish resync. All these three operations are initiated by the application.

In the first step, the application send prepare resyncd to orchagent, and orchagent just freeze its read operation, and also mark all the data stale. In the second step, application populates the full table. In the third step, application sends finish resync signal, and orchagent does the state reconciliation.

Such common table-level semantic simplify application development, we can simplify the fpmsync and neighsync, they do not need to implement comparison logic themselves. 

@rodnymolina , the signal is still give by fpmsyncd, orchagent cannot/do not need to figure out the reconnect event between zebra and fpmsyncd

@rodnymolina , can you explain kernel-routing-reconciliation, I am missing the context.

@zhenggen-xu , in this proposal, the owner is still application, the applications when to start the state reconciliation, swss just make it simply for the application to dump the table and resync.

@jipanyang , such service can be used for many different table where the user just want to dump a new table to the db without worrying about doing diff himself. For example, this can be use to handle those init json configuration cases.
